H0.text: Plant cells are the type of cells in which prophase is preceded by a preprophase stage.

H1.text: Brain cells are the type of cells in which prophase is preceded by a preprophase stage.

H2.text: Hair and nail cells are the type of cells in which prophase is preceded by a preprophase stage.

H3.text: Egg cells are the type of cells in which prophase is preceded by a preprophase stage.

A4.text: In plant cells only, prophase is preceded by a preprophase stage.
